                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 25010/36.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Italian Chargé</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-07-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 22, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 869.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The department has received your note of the 12th
                    instant, inclosing a copy of the warrant of arrest, issued June 13 last, by the
                    examining magistrate of the civil and criminal court of Como against Mr. Porter
                    Charlton.</p>
                <p>In reply I have the honor to inform you that the entire matter is now in the
                    hands of the court, to whom all documents, papers, etc., which the Italian
                    Government may have to offer in the case should now be presented.</p>
                <p>The copy of the warrant is returned herewith.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
